---
const steps = [
	{
		title: '1. Choose the matter type',
		copy: 'Start with the right lane so injury screening, legal guidance, and document consultations do not get treated like the same request.',
	},
	{
		title: '2. Send only the core facts',
		copy: 'Most people finish in 2 to 4 minutes. The form asks for the minimum details needed for fit, timing, and next-step review.',
	},
	{
		title: '3. Get the right follow-up',
		copy: 'Personal injury matters are screened for fit first. Other matters that fit usually move next to an email with scheduling instructions for the $100 30-minute consultation path.',
	},
];
---

<div class="panel intake-panel">
	<p class="mini-kicker">Intake Path</p>
	<h2 class="mini-title">How requests usually move.</h2>
	<p class="mini-copy">Attorney-led review from the Tulsa office, with most requests reviewed within 1 business day.</p>
	<ol class="intake-steps">
		{
			steps.map((step) => (
				<li>
					<strong>{step.title}</strong>
					<span>{step.copy}</span>
				</li>
			))
		}
	</ol>
	<p class="mini-copy">Submitting intake does not create an attorney-client relationship, but it does move the matter into the firm review queue.</p>
</div>
